    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Indian architecture, a semicircular ornamental step with a half-moon shape used at shrine portals. Literally, 'moonstone,' in Indian architecture; ardhacandra; moonstone; asvapada.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
